The 18th “World Beverage Innovation Awards” is an award jointly held by FoodBev Media and Brau Beviale. Totally 279 works of 22 different types from 25 countries were attracted to participate in the competition. On October 15, the list of the finalists was released, and the list of the final winners will be released on line on November 11 (British Summer Time). We see that the LP28 sugar-free yoghurt of Healing Forest entered for the next round of competition of the Best Milk Drink; “GOGO Wuhan” marketing entered for the next round of competition of the Best Marketing Activity; the packaging jointed designed by Pepsi and the new media of People’s Daily entered for the next round of competition of the Best Packaging Design/Label. According to Laura Nettle, the senior director of marketing of FoodBev Media, we are very glad to celebrate the 18th year of the annual World Beverage Innovation Awards with Brau Beviale. We’ve seen the trend of the drink industry with the sustainable innovations of the industry, including new flavors, new concepts and new functions in brands, packaging and manufacturing. World Beverage Innovation Awards highly praised the most ambitious new products and new development among new and old brands of the beverage industry all over the whole world. The followings are the complete list of the finalists of each type. The technology developed by Ardagh Group can melt 100% of recycled glass to new bottles. The bags in cases are filled with water, and the packing boxes can be recycled 100%, which reduces 66% of packages and carbon emission of 97%. LatCub is 100% biodegradable, with less use of paper, free from glue or tape leading to hazards to the environment. The technology developed by Ardagh Group can melt 100% of recycled glass to new bottles. The list of the final winners will be released in YouTube channel of FoodBev Media on November 11 (British Summer Time), and FBIF will report it for you continuously; coming soon!
